"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A practice of hospitality used by Jesus Christ to express his servanthood.</p>\n<h2>Foot-washing as a sign of courteous hospitality</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:4\">GEN 18:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:2\">GEN 19:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:21\">JDG 19:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:41\">1SA 25:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:44\">LUK 7:44</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ washes his disciples' feet</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:3-John13:5\">JHN 13:3–13:5</a></strong> <em>The washing of feet was a lowly task normally performed by a servant.</em></p>\n<h3>As an example of servanthood for his followers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:14\">JHN 13:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:26-Matt20:27\">MAT 20:26–20:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:44-Mark10:45\">MRK 10:44–10:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:26-Luke22:27\">LUK 22:26–22:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:10\">1TI 5:10</a></p>\n<h3>As a symbol of spiritual cleansing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:6-John13:10\">JHN 13:6–13:10</a></strong></p>",
